Operational Risk – Markets & Treasury
Operational Risk – Markets & Treasury
Location:  Singapore
Salary:  SGD190000 - SGD220000 per annumOur Client
A global bank with a diverse range of banking activities is looking for an experienced operational risk manager to join their treasury, credit and investment markets business, providing an oversight on operational risk management for the business. The incumbent will be ensuring identification, assessment and governance of risk in the department.
Ensure alignment of Operational Risk policies with group risk framework
Ensure strong operational risk culture within the business
Implement concise operational risk management plan for the business
Act as the main point of control for the risk exposure for the business
Implement policies and controls for the effective monitoring of processes and risk
Identify and assess process gaps, improving control measures where necessary
Put in place measures to reduce risk of operational failure
Review risk assessments conducted by business risk team
Review and approve high-risk business, ensuring risk classification is up to date
Work with business managers to review business processes which may exceed standard risk exposure levels
Review and approve operational risks of new products
Prepare and analyse operational risk loss events
Requirements
At least 10 years of operational risk management experience in treasury, markets and/or investment banking
Experienced in working in Singapore is compulsory
Strong communication and presentation skills
Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to manage multiple stakeholders
If you are interested in exploring this role further, please send your resume to Mabel Gao at or call directly on +65 3157 1208 for a confidential discussion.
License: Argyll Scott Singapore Pte Ltd (11C3721)
